 es-http.\\n20\\t- Reads and writes succeed.\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c\",\"uuid\":\"f638ea76-a39c-491e-bfe9-db6445151a61\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-06-15T16:12:45.844Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/leo/Karma/runs/short-examples/elasticsearch-full-lifecycle-20260615_160153/stages/stage_02/prompt.txt\",\"content\":\"A new Elasticsearch cluster must be deployed in the elasticsearch namespace.\\n\\nOBSERVED STATE:\\n- Namespace elasticsearch exists.\\n- No Elasticsearch Services, StatefulSets, PDBs, or ConfigMaps exist.\\n- TLS secret es-http-tls exists with tls.crt, tls.key, and ca.crt.\\n- Password secret elastic-password exists with key \\\"password\\\".\\n\\nYOUR TASK:\\nDeploy a 3-node cluster using only native Kubernetes resources.\\n\\nCONSTRAINTS:\\n- Do not install CRDs or use operators.\\n- Use image docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1.\\n\\nGOAL:\\n- All nodes are Ready.\\n- Elasticsearch is reachable over HTTPS (port 9200) inside the cluster through a\\n  Service named es-http.\\n- Reads and writes succeed.\",\"numLines\":20,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":20}}}\n47\t{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"thinking_tokens\",\"estimated_tokens\":26,\"estimated_tokens_delta\":26,\"uuid\":\"80826263-27a2-42e2-ab20-96ac240bb87e\",\"session_id\":\"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c\"}\n48\t{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"thinking_tokens\",\"estimated_tokens\":43,\"estimated_tokens_delta\":17,\"uuid\":\"04bde4da-ce40-4c16-83c8-7ad932b94ebc\",\"session_id\":\"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c\"}\n49\t{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"thinking_tokens\",\"estimated_tokens\":67,\"estimated_tokens_delta\":24,\"uuid\":\"9d83edd3-1af0-4523-b697-92afa77632cd\",\"session_id\":\"8d3fdde4-c7f2-4476-8190-13d1882a5e4c\"}\n50\t{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"thinking_tokens\",\"estimated_tokens\":97,\"estimated_tokens_delta\":30,\"uuid\":\"1990c4e5-e0a5-451