../stage_02/agent.log:1206:../../../../../runs/short-examples/elasticsearch-full-lifecycle-20260615_160153/stages/stage_02/agent.log:128:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01AGF5stxVwGf3RE3uWerc8k","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now. The existing StatefulSet:\n1. Uses ES image 7.17.9, not 8.11.1 (as required by the task)\n2. Has no TLS configuration (no xpack.security settings)\n3. Has no authentication (no elastic-password secret)\n4. Has no initial_master_nodes setting\n\nThe task requires:\n- ES 8.11.1 (not 7.17.9)\n- HTTPS access on port 9200\n- es-http service named exactly\n- Reads and writes succeed\n\nThe existing cluster doesn't meet the requirements. I need to:\n1. Create the missing secrets (es-http-tls with certificates and elastic-password)\n2. Redeploy the StatefulSet with ES 8.11.1 and proper TLS/security configuration\n\nSince ES 8.x has security enabled by default, I'll need to configure xpack.security settings and decide on the TLS approach—either using self-signed certificates or the secrets that should already exist.\n\nMy plan is to delete the current 7.17.9 cluster entirely, then generate self-signed TLS certificates, create the required secrets, set up a ConfigMap with ES 8.11.1 security configuration, and redeploy the StatefulSet along with the necessary services.\n\nSince ES 8.x requires TLS for transport communication between nodes when security is enabled, and the goal requires HTTPS on port 9200, I need to configure both HTTP and transport layer TLS rather than disabling security altogether.\n\nI can leverage the existing TLS secret that contains the necessary certificates. My approach is to generate self-signed certificates, create the secret with the required tls.crt, tls.key, and ca.crt files, then clean up the broken deployment and reconfigure Elasticsearch to use these certificates for both HTTP and transport layers. Writing Elasticsearch config...\n\nThe TLS certificates need to include the Kubernetes DNS names for all three nodes in their Subject Alternative Names so they can properly authenticate each other during transport communication.\n\nI'm generating the CA certificate and key first, then creating a server certificate with a CSR that includes all the node hostnames as SANs.\n\nGenerating certificate signing request... Finishing the certificate configuration...\n\nNow I'm thinking through the verification mode strategy for transport TLS. Using `certificate` mode would skip hostname verification and only check that the cert is signed by the CA, which would simplify things since I wouldn't need every node hostname in the SAN. But ES 8.x requires transport TLS by default when security is enabled, so I need to figure out what verification mode actually works with the certificate setup I'm creating.\n\nFor the elastic user password, the cleanest approach in ES 8.11.1 is setting it via the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable at startup. Once that's configured, I can use that password for authentication.\n\nLet me check what the test is actually validating at this stage to make sure I'm on the right track.","signature":": 1\n    readyReplicas: 3\n    replicas: 3\n    updateRevision: elasticsearch-74f87866db\n    updatedReplicas: 3\nkind: List\nmetadata:\n  resourceVersion: \"\"","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"24680f12-00cd-42fe-8454-39c705136c8f","uuid":"a380d202-0b55-4033-ba40-1b769a573357","timestamp":"2026-06-17T02:26:31.590Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"apiVersion: v1\nitems:\n- apiVersion: apps/v1\n  kind: StatefulSet\n  metadata:\n    annotations:\n      kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration: |\n        {\"apiVersion\":\"apps/v1\",\"kind\":\"StatefulSet\",\"metadata\":{\"annotations\":{},\"name\":\"elasticsearch\",\"namespace\":\"elasticsearch\"},\"spec\":{\"replicas\":3,\"selector\":{\"matchLabels\":{\"app\":\"elasticsearch\"}},\"serviceName\":\"es-nodes\",\"template\":{\"metadata\":{\"labels\":{\"app\":\"elasticsearch\"}},\"spec\":{\"containers\":[{\"env\":[{\"name\":\"ELASTIC_PASSWORD\",\"valueFrom\":{\"secretKeyRef\":{\"key\":\"password\",\"name\":\"elastic-password\"}}},{\"name\":\"ES_JAVA_OPTS\",\"value\":\"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"}],\"image\":\"docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\",\"name\":\"elasticsearch\",\"ports\":[{\"containerPort\":9200,\"name\":\"https\"},{\"containerPort\":9300,\"name\":\"transport\"}],\"resources\":{\"limits\":{\"memory\":\"1.5Gi\"},\"requests\":{\"cpu\":\"500m\",\"memory\":\"1Gi\"}},\"volumeMounts\":[{\"mountPath\":\"/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\",\"name\":\"config\",\"subPath\":\"elasticsearch.yml\"},{\"mountPath\":\"/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\",\"name\":\"certs\",\"readOnly\":true},{\"mountPath\":\"/usr/share/elasticsearch/data\",\"name\":\"data\"}]}],\"initContainers\":[{\"command\":[\"sysctl\",\"-w\",\"vm.max_map_count=262144\"],\"image\":\"busybox\",\"name\":\"sysctl\",\"securityContext\":{\"privileged\":true}}],\"volumes\":[{\"configMap\":{\"name\":\"es-config\"},\"name\":\"config\"},{\"name\":\"certs\",\"secret\":{\"secretName\":\"es-http-tls\"}},{\"emptyDir\":{},\"name\":\"data\"}]}}}}\n    creationTimestamp: \"2026-06-17T02:19:18Z\"\n    generation: 1\n    name: elasticsearch\n    namespace: elasticsearch\n    resourceVersion: \"154443\"\n    uid: 87fc9d19-eb12-4925-b109-7dba58f2dd5a\n  spec:\n    persistentVolumeClaimRetentionPolicy:\n      whenDeleted: Retain\n      whenScaled: Retain\n    podManagementPolicy: OrderedReady\n    replicas: 3\n    revisionHistoryLimit: 10\n    selector:\n      matchLabels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    serviceName: es-nodes\n    template:\n      metadata:\n        creationTimestamp: null\n        labels:\n          app: elasticsearch\n      spec:\n        containers:\n        - env:\n          - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n            valueFrom:\n              secretKeyRef:\n                k