../stage_02/agent.log:1264:../../../../../runs/error-prone-examples/elasticsearch-scale-users-audit-20260616_101353/stages/stage_01/agent.log:54:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018fGiYDBi94i428NKgNL3wr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll create the Kubernetes manifests for a 3-node Elasticsearch cluster:\n\n1. ConfigMap for Elasticsearch configuration\n2. Service for inter-node communication (headless)\n3. Service for external access (es-http)\n4. StatefulSet with 3 nodes\n5. PodDisruptionBudget\n\nKey considerations for ES 8.x:\n- Need to configure TLS for HTTPS\n- Need to set up the password from the secret\n- For Elasticsearch 8.11.1, HTTPS and xpack.security are enabled by default, so I need to configure both the HTTP layer TLS using the es-http-tls secret and set up transport TLS for inter-node communication, which I can either use the same certificates for or configure separately.\n- Since I don't know what domains the existing tls.crt covers, I might need to generate a separate self-signed certificate for transport TLS or disable verification if the certificate doesn't include the internal service names. options here: I can use `verification_mode: none` for a simpler but less secure setup, or `verification_mode: certificate` to validate the cert without checking hostnames. For ES 8.x, I'll go with certificate verification since it's the recommended middle ground when the TLS cert doesn't have the specific node hostnames in its SANs. Now I'm structuring the manifest with a ConfigMap for the elasticsearch.yml configuration...\n\nWriting Elasticsearch config... Writing the manifest... Writing Kubernetes services and policies... Finishing the StatefulSet configuration with environment variables for the Elasticsearch password and JVM settings, then mounting the configuration files, certificates, and persistent data volume, along with resource requests and limits for the container.\n\nThe pod naming from the StatefulSet with the headless service will create `es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2` which matches what I'm setting in `cluster.initial_master_nodes`, and the `node.name` environment variable will use the hostname to align with that. The headless service DNS will also work for `discovery.seed_hosts`. I should make sure the `elasticsearch.yml` ConfigMap uses proper YAML formatting that Elasticsearch expects.\n\nWriting config YAML...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":29002,"output_tokens":3533,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":3533,"cache_read_input_tokens":29002,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":{"applied_edits":[]}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88aa9a3a-e056-408c-84ff-72f2233e54a4","uuid":"02ef014b-75ec-460b-bb8d-000000000000","request_id":"req_011Cc6mWbkhZEUKphdbo6Y8a"}
../stage_02/agent.log:1265:../../../../../runs/error-prone-examples/elasticsearch-scale-users-audit-20260616_101353/stages/stage_01/agent.log:71:{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EDGcbfLCMBjQukf22UU8WF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0112fG8ABFuEMYgyMKCu5Afb","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/error-prone-examples/elasticsearch-scale-users-audit-20260616_101353/stages/stage_01/es-cluster.yaml","content":"---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: es-cluster\n    node.name: ${HOSTNAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    discovery.seed_hosts:\n      - es-headless.elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes:\n      - es-0\n      - es-1\n      - es-2\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl:\n      enabled: true\n      key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n      certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n      certificate_authorities:\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl:\n      enabled: true\n      verification_mode: certificate\n      key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n      certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n      certificate_authorities:\n        - /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-headless\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: http\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n    - name: transport\n      port: 9300\n      targetPort: 9300\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n    - name: https\n      port: 9200\n      targetPort: 9200\n---\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: es-pdb\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  maxUnavailable: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-headless\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      securityContext:\n        fsGroup: 1000\n        runAsUser: 1000\n      containers:\n        - name: elasticsearch\n          image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n          ports:\n            - containerPort: 9200\n              name: http\n            - containerPort: 9300\n              name: transport\n          env:\n            - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n              valueFrom:\n                secretKeyRef:\n                  name: elastic-password\n                  key: password\n            - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n              value: \"-Xms512m -Xmx512m\"\n          volumeMounts:\n            - name: es-config\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n              subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n            - name: es-certs\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n              readOnly: true\n            - name: es-data\n              mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n          readinessProbe:\n            exec:\n              command:\n                - bash\n                - -c\n                - |\n                  curl -sf --cacert /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt \\\n                    -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" \\\n                    https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health?wait_for_status=yellow \\\n                    > /dev/null\n            initialDelaySeconds: 30\n            periodSeconds: 10\n            timeoutSeconds: 10\n            failureThreshold: 6\n          resources:\n            requests:\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\n              cpu: \"500m\"\n            limits:\n              memory: \"2Gi\"\n      volumes:\n        - name: es-config\n          configMap:\n            name: es-config\n        - name: es-certs\n          secret:\n            secretName: es-http-tls\n        - name: es-data\n          emptyDir: {}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":292,"cache_read_input_tokens":32615,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":292},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"88aa9a3a-e056-408c-84ff-72f2233e54a4","uuid":"34fdf3a6-c558-4ca1-8bf3-cbf5b022ad06","request_id":"req_011Cc6mh1KKDxmtrr7rfUWL4"}
